      "digest": {
        "published": "2005-01-10",
        "description": "Multiple integer overflows in xzgv 0.8 and earlier allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via images with large width and height values, which trigger a heap-based buffer overflow, as demonstrated in the read_prf_file function in readprf.c.  NOTE: CVE-2004-0994 and CVE-2004-1095 identify sets of bugs that only partially overlap, despite having the same developer.  Therefore, they should be regarded as distinct.",
        "title": "debian debian_linux Buffer Overflow",
        "vendor": "zgv",
        "product": "xzgv_image_viewer",
        "attack_type": "Buffer Overflow",
        "cvss_max": 10.0
      },
      "cve": {
        "id": "CVE-2004-0994",
        "sourceIdentifier": "cve@mitre.org",
        "published": "2005-01-10T05:00:00.000",
        "lastModified": "2026-04-16T00:27:16.627",
        "vulnStatus": "Modified",
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "Multiple integer overflows in xzgv 0.8 and earlier allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via images with large width and height values, which trigger a heap-based buffer overflow, as demonstrated in the read_prf_file function in readprf.c.  NOTE: CVE-2004-0994 and CVE-2004-1095 identify sets of bugs that only partially overlap, despite having the same developer.  Therefore, they should be regarded as distinct."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "Múltiples desbordamientos de enteros en xzgv 0.8 y anteriores permiten a atacantes remotos ejecutar código de su elección mediante imágenes con valores de anchura y altura largos, lo que dispara un desbordamiento de búfer basado en el montón, como se ha demostrado en la función read_prf_file de readprf.c.\r\nNota: CAN-2004-0994 y CAN-2004-1095 identifican grupos de errores que se solapan sólo parcialemte, a pesar de tener el mismo desarrollador. Por lo tanto, deberían considerarse como diferentes."
          }
        ],
